<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:328.49px" class="cls_006"><span class="cls_006">Introduction</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:367.13px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">The internet plays a more significant role in your dental practice than you</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:381.77px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">think. 98% of customers choose a dentist from the first page of Google. Many</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:396.29px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">customers also check reviews and ratings before booking an appointment.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:410.83px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Does your dental practice have enough online reviews to help you get new</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:425.35px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">customers and beat the competition?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:454.51px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">In this e-book we will deep dive into online reviews and why they are</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:469.03px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">essential for your dental practice.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:498.07px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">To begin with, here are 3 things that you must do as a dentist, to get more customers and</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:512.71px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">build long-lasting relationships with the existing ones:</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:541.75px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">1.  Develop a deep understanding of your customers’ wants and needs</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:556.27px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">2.  Address all customer issues immediately</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:570.79px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">3.  Ensure happy customers’ voices get heard</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:599.98px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">How? By harnessing the power of online reviews with a comprehensive online</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:614.50px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">reputation management platform.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:647.14px" class="cls_006"><span class="cls_006">How do online reviews work?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:685.90px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Online reviews are a form of User Generated Content</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:700.42px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">(UGC) that existing and loyal customers can share on public</span></div>
</div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:50%;margin-left:-306px;top:802px;width:612px;height:792px;border-style:outset;overflow:hidden">
<div style="position:absolute;left:0px;top:0px">
<img src="{{ asset('img/background6.jpg')}}" width=612 height=792></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:71.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">sites such as Google and Facebook. These sites typically</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:85.82px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">structure feedback as open-ended commentary alongside</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:100.34px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">a rating from 1-5 stars.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:129.50px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">After a customer posts a review for a dental practice, it’s tied</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:144.02px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">to that practice’s profile and visible to the public. Any</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:158.54px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">potential customers who visit that review site can see all the</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:173.18px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">reviews posted for that dental practice, both positive and</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:187.70px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">negative. In most cases, reviews cannot be deleted by the</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:202.22px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">dentist; they can only be removed by the review site itself</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:216.74px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">if they violate the site’s policies.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:249.41px" class="cls_006"><span class="cls_006">Why are online reviews important for a small business?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:288.17px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">First, online reviews are displayed in search engine</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:302.69px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">results and have a huge impact on local Search</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:317.21px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Engine Optimization (SEO). Local SEO is a primary</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:331.73px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">driver of customer acquisition: 90% of customers choose</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:346.37px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">a dental practice on page 1 of search results, and</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:360.89px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">they favor the local results . When it comes to</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:375.41px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">reviews, having a high volume of positive ones</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:389.93px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">works wonders for your local SEO.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:419.11px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">• Review Quantity (number of reviews)</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:433.63px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">• Review Velocity (how frequent reviews are posted)</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:448.15px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">• Review Diversity (the breadth of sites reviews are posted on)</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:477.31px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">A substantial portion (13%) of the 200+ factors in</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:491.83px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Google’s search engine algorithm involve review</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:506.35px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">signals such as:</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:535.39px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Both Google and customers value online reviews, and the proof is in the numbers:</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:564.55px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Dentists with positive reviews get up to 200% more customers than dentists with</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:593.62px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">no reviews (WebRepublic)</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:622.78px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">• 1-3 bad online reviews are enough to deter the majority (67%) of customers from</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:651.82px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">booking an appointment (Lightspeed Research)</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:680.98px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">• 92% of customers will want to consult a dentist if they have at least a 4-star</span></div>
</div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:50%;margin-left:-306px;top:1604px;width:612px;height:792px;border-style:outset;overflow:hidden">
<div style="position:absolute;left:0px;top:0px">
<img src="{{ asset('img/background6.jpg')}}" width=612 height=792></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:71.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">rating (Cornell University)</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:100.34px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">• 88% of customers trust online reviews as much as personal recommendations</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:129.50px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">(BrightLocal Consumer Survey)</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:158.54px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">This means that local dentists can compete against national chains on a local SEO</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:173.18px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">level -- and potentially win.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:202.22px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">In addition to their marketing power, online reviews also provide invaluable insight into</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:216.74px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">brand perception and overall customer experience. We’ll cover how to use online reviews</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:231.26px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">to drive customer experience improvement later in this eBook.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:264.05px" class="cls_006"><span class="cls_006">Focus On Site Most Important to Your Business</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:302.69px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Google and Facebook carry more authority than most, so reviews on these sites are</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:317.21px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">valuable for any business. Google reviews have the power to bring your dental practice</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:331.73px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">to the top of search and Maps results, while Facebook, with more than 1.4 billion</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:346.37px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">monthly active users, puts your practice in front of a massive audience of potential</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:360.89px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">customers. customers are often already logged in, so it’s easy to ask them for a review here.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:389.93px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">In addition to these large sites, you should include review sites relevant to the dental</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:404.45px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">industry in your review management strategy. How can these niche sites make an</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:419.11px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">impact?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:448.15px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Let’s say a customer searches for “dentists near me” on Google. High up in results will be</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:462.67px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">dental-specific sites like HealthGrades and ZocDoc. customers visiting these sites are</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:477.31px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">further along the path of shortlisting a dentist and know exactly what they’re looking</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:491.83px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">for, in a dental practice. Therefore, the conversion rate is much higher once they view</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:506.35px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">your dental practice’s profile on one of these industry-specific sites.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:538.99px" class="cls_006"><span class="cls_006">How to Fetch Online Reviews</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:577.78px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Authentically. As tempting as it might be, do not offer your</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:592.30px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">customers incentives in exchange for a review. Not only does</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:606.82px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">this lead to biased or insincere reviews that don’t</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:621.34px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">accurately reflect the customer’s experience; this practice is</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:635.86px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">also frowned upon or even forbidden by most review sites.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:665.02px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Promptly. It’s best to ask your customers for a review</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:679.54px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">immediately after their treatment is completed. This</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:694.06px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">ensures your practice is still top of mind and makes your</span></div>
</div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:50%;margin-left:-306px;top:2406px;width:612px;height:792px;border-style:outset;overflow:hidden">
<div style="position:absolute;left:0px;top:0px">
<img src="{{ asset('img/background6.jpg')}}" width=612 height=792></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:71.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">outreach come across as relevant and helpful rather</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:85.82px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">than disruptive.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:114.98px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Seamlessly. Meet your customers where they are. Often this</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:129.50px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">is their smartphones. Your review request messages</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:144.02px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">should be compatible across all desktop and mobile</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:158.54px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">devices and should involve as few steps as possible. This</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:173.18px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">way, wherever your customers are, reviewing your practice is</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:187.70px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">an easy, seamless experience for them.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:202.22px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Consistently. Your review generation strategy must</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:216.74px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">be ongoing for it to be effective. Most customers only</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:231.26px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">find a review relevant if it was written in the last 2-3</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:245.93px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">months, so you need a constant stream of fresh</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:258.53px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">reviews to prove your credibility to potential customers .</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:293.09px" class="cls_006"><span class="cls_006">Review Management</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:331.73px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">To earn your customers’ loyalty, it’s imperative that you</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:346.37px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">respond to both positive and negative online reviews. A</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:360.89px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">recent study revealed that 70% of consumers, across</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:375.41px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">industries, changed their opinion about a business after</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:389.93px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">the business responded to their review.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:419.11px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Depending on how many reviews you’re getting,</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:433.63px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">responding to each one might be impossible, but you can</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:448.15px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">set a realistic response ratio for your support team, such</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:462.67px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">as 1 response for every 4 reviews. Your responses should</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:477.31px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">be personal, respectful, and helpful.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:508.03px" class="cls_007"><span class="cls_007">Positive Reviews</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:530.11px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Just because a customer was happy with their experience doesn’t mean your job is done.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:544.63px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Follow up with happy customers to thank them for their feedback and show you genuinely</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:559.15px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">care about their satisfaction.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:588.22px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">3 things to remember while responding to positive customer reviews:</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:617.38px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">1.  Thank the customer for their review</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:631.90px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">2.  Add a personal touch if possible</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:646.42px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">3.  Express your hope that they return</span></div>
</div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:50%;margin-left:-306px;top:3208px;width:612px;height:792px;border-style:outset;overflow:hidden">
<div style="position:absolute;left:0px;top:0px">
<img src="{{ asset('img/background6.jpg')}}" width=612 height=792></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:71.54px" class="cls_007"><span class="cls_007">Negative reviews</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:108.14px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Negative reviews can actually benefit your practice if managed correctly. First, negative</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:122.66px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">reviews show you what you can improve--at a very low cost. The only potential price</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:137.18px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">you pay is losing new prospective customers if they see that negative review. That price</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:151.70px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">can be avoided if you are diligent about responding to negative feedback.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:180.86px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">If you respond quickly enough, you can turn a frustrating situation into an overall</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:195.38px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">positive customer experience. You might even get the customer to take down their negative</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:209.90px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">review.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:239.06px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Even if the customer is in the wrong, it’s important not to respond defensively. This only</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:253.61px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">escalates conflicts and makes you appear unprofessional and unconcerned. Treat</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:268.13px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">every customer’s complaint as equally valid and respond thoughtfully and constructively.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:282.65px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">If you insist on correcting their misunderstanding, do so calmly and sympathetically.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:311.81px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">4 things to remember while responding to negative customer reviews:</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:340.85px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">1.  Apologize</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:355.37px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">2.  Offer a reasonable solution</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:370.01px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">3.  Follow-up privately</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:384.53px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">4.  Stay HIPAA compliant if your customer is your patient</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:417.19px" class="cls_006"><span class="cls_006">Final Words</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:455.83px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Online reviews are changing the way customers select dentists. If</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:470.47px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">managed properly, online reviews can help dentists improve their</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:484.99px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">online presence, foster trust and loyalty, and get more customers.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:514.03px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Both positive and negative reviews can make a positive impact on</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:528.55px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">your brand. Just as important as regularly collecting new reviews is</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:543.19px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">diligently responding to them, promoting them, and regularly</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:557.71px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">gathering and analyzing insights from them to improve the customer</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:572.23px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">experience on an ongoing basis.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:601.42px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Finally, it is important to choose an online review management</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:615.94px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">platform that fits your customer base and services. Be sure your review</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:630.46px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">generation approach fits your customers’ habits, and that your staff is</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:644.98px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">prepared to efficiently manage incoming customer feedback.</span></div>
</div>
